Total: 57 cards   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This deck runs around mainly, as said before, stealing stuff and wiping the other player&#39;s side of the board clear with Core Grag.<br>
This deck has several mean combos and surprises. First is a Turn combo with Turn, Koil, Zungg, and sometimes Borgor, which lowers a creature&#39;s energy below it&#39;s starting energy so it can be stolen with Turn. Another combo is an energy combo with Trask, Vrill, Zungg, and Raveled Drush. You use Zungg, Raveled Drush, and sometimes Vrill&#39;s powers to make a gargantuan Trask!<br>
Also, the deck&#39;s one major surprise is it&#39;s rather boring-looking second Magi, Golthub. While he&#39;s a Core/Bograth Magi, only energizes for 4, and has no starting cards in this deck, he still has won several games for me. First, he can play Crushing Darkness, which is a major factor. Second, his power, which is often ignored,  is: &quot;Mire: Choose any one region. Defeat Golthub. Destroy all non-Magi cards of the chosen region from play.&quot; Basically, with Maelstrom, Core Grag, or Vaporize, or all of the above, the Magi has no energy on him/her, and dies with a bang. Also good for last-ditch destruction of an evil opposing combo on the board, if nothing else works. The nice thing about this is that then you get Morag coming out, with an energize rate of 7, and both barrels blasting. By this time, you should have a sizable hand and many options available to you. Then you can destroy your opponent mercilessly.<br>
<br>
The one thing that you need to watch out for with this deck is playing against other Core decks, or other thief decks. But generally, this deck will hold its own against most everything. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
